name: Online ‚Äì Three Boons Yoga ‚Äì f.k.a. Jivamukti Berlin
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Online ‚Äì Three Boons Yoga ‚Äì f.k.a. Jivamukti Berlin', 'description': 'Formerly known as Jivamukti Yoga Berlin, Three Boons Yoga Berlin in Mitte and Kreuzberg have been independent Jivamukti Yoga schools since 2009, offering, at (pre-Corona) times, up to 150 yoga classes a week. The vast majority of these classes have been Jivamukti Yoga classes, and the vast majority of our teachers have been Jivamukti Yoga teachers, some of the best-trained and most experienced out there. With our new name, nothing of the above really changes, except for, well, the name: You will still able to access the same high-quality Jivamukti Yoga classes with some of the best and coolest yoga teachers out there. Hopefully, we will see each other again very soon in a yoga class in one of our beautiful studios, which we have been busy renovating and improving massively during the past months. And for the time being, let‚Äôs stay in touch through Three Boons Yoga Online offering more than 50 Live-Stream classes per week. The Jivamukti Yoga method developed out of the vibrant creative scene in lower Manhattan, and for decades the New York Jivamukti school was one of the busiest, most popular and most innovative yoga centers in the world. Described as ‚ÄúThe Wild Child of Yoga" by Paper magazine, Jivamukti always attracted highly creative, ambitious and vital students, drawn to the vigorous Hatha Yoga classes and the deeply spiritual sense of community found at the center. Evolving to Three Boons Yoga Berlin allows us to stay local and keeps us independent and true to ourselves, enabling us to continue to embody what we loved about Jivamukti Yoga, once upon a time, when we adopted the name Jivamukti Yoga Berlin: Being hot, hip and holy Wild Children of Yoga, independent of global policies and corporations. After all, liberation is what the way of the Jivanmukta is all about.', 'address': {'@type': 'PostalAddress', 'addressLocality': 'Berlin, Germany', 'addressCountry': 'Germany', 'postalCode': '10119', 'streetAddress': 'Brunnenstra√üe 28'}, 'telephone': '', 'geo': {'@type': 'GeoCoordinates', 'latitude': '52.533302', 'longitude': '13.398998'}, 'priceRange': '-', 'image': 'https://storage.googleapis.com/download/storage/v1/b/usc-pro-uscweb-live-media/o/de-live%2Foriginal_2000x1125_Bild1_1616513234360847_admin.png?alt=media'}
description: Formerly known as Jivamukti Yoga Berlin, Three Boons Yoga Berlin in Mitte and Kreuzberg have been independent Jivamukti Yoga schools since 2009, offering, at (pre-Corona) times, up to 150 yoga classes a week. The vast majority of these classes have been Jivamukti Yoga classes, and the vast majority of our teachers have been Jivamukti Yoga teachers, some of the best-trained and most experienced out there. With our new name, nothing of the above really changes, except for, well, the name: You will still able to access the same high-quality Jivamukti Yoga classes with some of the best and coolest yoga teachers out there. Hopefully, we will see each other again very soon in a yoga class in one of our beautiful studios, which we have been busy renovating and improving massively during the past months. And for the time being, let‚Äôs stay in touch through Three Boons Yoga Online offering more than 50 Live-Stream classes per week. The Jivamukti Yoga method developed out of the vibrant creative scene in lower Manhattan, and for decades the New York Jivamukti school was one of the busiest, most popular and most innovative yoga centers in the world. Described as ‚ÄúThe Wild Child of Yoga" by Paper magazine, Jivamukti always attracted highly creative, ambitious and vital students, drawn to the vigorous Hatha Yoga classes and the deeply spiritual sense of community found at the center. Evolving to Three Boons Yoga Berlin allows us to stay local and keeps us independent and true to ourselves, enabling us to continue to embody what we loved about Jivamukti Yoga, once upon a time, when we adopted the name Jivamukti Yoga Berlin: Being hot, hip and holy Wild Children of Yoga, independent of global policies and corporations. After all, liberation is what the way of the Jivanmukta is all about.

name: the dopamine studio
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'the dopamine studio', 'description': 'Step into the Dopamine Studio and immerse yourself in professionally guided classes, or simply unwind and rejuvenate in our invigorating Barrel Sauna and Ice Bath facility during one of our guided recovery sessions. DOPE Boxing courses: The ultimate fusion of boxing mastery and an exhilarating, sweat-inducing workout. Led by coaches with real-life boxing experience, our classes guarantee the highest level of instruction. Prepare for an adrenaline-pumping session where the focus is on learning the basics of boxing through partner work and pad training. Guaranteeing you a sweaty workout that will leave you with a delightful surge of dopamine. OBS: For DOPE boxing, you will need gloves and hand wraps: Either bring your own or conveniently purchase/rent them at our studio. DOPE Recovery: Recover like a pro in our urban jungle. In our barrel Sauna and Ice bath station, we host guided recovery sessions that will take you on a wild journey of hot and cold therapy to help you recover from any occasion, whether it's a long night out in Berlin or a hard week of workouts. New to fitness or returning after a break? No worries! Our courses cater to all levels, accommodating beginners and advanced individuals alike. Our dedicated coaches will ensure your well-being every step of the way. Any questions? Just reach out: info@thedopaminestudio.com. Our Vision: Dopamine Studio aspires to be more than just a gym. We are a gathering place for individuals united by their passion for fitness and movement. We believe in striking a balance between enjoying a few cold beverages on weekends and caring for our bodies, minds, and souls. Our classes are thoughtfully designed to foster connections through partner exercises and challenges. Our space offers an inviting environment to relax, have a coffee, and engage in friendly conversations before and after workouts. To promote a strong sense of community, we regularly host DOPE Socials and other community events, which you can read more about on our Instagram @thedopamine.studio. At Dopamine, we prioritize the safety and inclusivity of all our members, striving to create a community-driven space where everyone can find their own perfect way to experience a dopamine rush.', 'address': {'@type': 'PostalAddress', 'addressLocality': 'Berlin, Germany', 'addressCountry': 'Germany', 'postalCode': '10997', 'streetAddress': 'Schleusenufer 4'}, 'telephone': '', 'geo': {'@type': 'GeoCoordinates', 'latitude': '52.4979964', 'longitude': '13.4501632'}, 'priceRange': '-', 'image': 'https://storage.googleapis.com/download/storage/v1/b/usc-pro-uscweb-live-media/o/de-live%2Foriginal_1024x576_1_1704377728891727_admin.png?generation=1704377728953938&alt=media'}

metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'HYROX MITTE', 'description': 'GERMAN VERSION: Umgeben von Neubauten der Europa City & 5 min vom Berliner Hauptbahnhof ist Cycle Room Berlin 2021 entstanden. Mit Berliner Club Beats und neuster Stages Bike Ausstattung kann man hier mal abschalten und sich frei f√ºhlen. name: BerimbArte @ La Caminada
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'BerimbArte @ La Caminada', 'description': 'Capoeira is an Afro-Brazilian martial art. It combines various self defense and fighting techniques with rhythm, dance and acrobatics. The traditional music is a big part of the Capoeira culture and is also practiced and performed by the participants. The Capoeira group BerimbArte e.V. was founded in 2006 in Berlin. The name means ‚ÄúArt of the Berimbau‚Äù, the main instrument and a symbol of Capoeira. The group arranges a various amount of workshops, competitions and excursions every year. Privately the participants often meet up for additional trainings in the park, barbecue or just for beer and wine. The founder and main trainer of the group is Mestre Canguru (Lourival Pereira dos Santos). He started training Capoeira in 1989 in Brazil with the age of 12. In 1998 he moved to Berlin to bring the Capoeira culture to Europe. Today he has more than 25 years experience as a trainer and additional experience in BJJ and Muay Boran. No matter if newbie or veteran, everyone is welcome! Spoken languages in our group so far are German, English, Portuguese, French, Spanish and Italian.', 'address': {'@type': 'PostalAddress', 'addressLocality': 'Berlin, Germany', 'addressCountry': 'Germany', 'postalCode': '10967', 'streetAddress': 'B√∂ckhstra√üe 21'}, 'telephone': '', 'geo': {'@type': 'GeoCoordinates', 'latitude': '52.4931567', 'longitude': '13.4198872'}, 'priceRange': '-', 'image': 'https://storage.googleapis.com/download/storage/v1/b/usc-pro-uscweb-live-media/o/de-live%2Foriginal_1280x720_hvi6tiqvvy1va2amxuot_1733081671653760.png?generation=1733081671756728&alt=media'}

name: Rocycle Berlin F'hain
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Rocycle Berlin F'hain', 'description': 'Rocycle is an effective, sweaty and fun workout that takes your mind off everything. We make our community fit and happy. Every day. Every ride. Our full-body 45- & 60-minute workouts on a bike are uplifting experiences. Set to candlelight and fueled by epic beats, our classes are made to give you that natural high. Ride the energy of the pack as you pedal out of the saddle for most of the class, training your core and raising your heart rate. You will train your upper body with hand weights and handlebar push-ups, then finish with head-to-toe stretching. Our workouts take your mind off everything, as you feel the endorphins rushing through your body. In an hour, you will walk out completely revitalized. Music is our mantra: Each class rocks a unique playlist handpicked by your instructor, from deep house and electronic to pop, hip-hop, and French house. Feel the chills from each song, let the beats lift you up and get carried away by the energy of the tracks. It can get a little emotional in here ‚Äì go with it! We like to call it the happiness effect. Get ready to pamper yourself in the changing rooms: After the class, drop your shoes and towel in the designated bins and drift towards the showers. We've made sure that you can really pamper yourself in our changing rooms. Luxurious fresh towels and Zenology‚Äôs line of organic care products await you ‚Äì including body wash, shampoo, conditioner and body lotion. name: Urban Gladiators
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Urban Gladiators', 'description': 'Strange Of Motion offers a variety of movement classes, designed to help you explore your bodies capabilities to move in a structured yet playful way. And for the time being, let‚Äôs stay in touch through Three Boons Yoga Online offering more than 50 Live-Stream classes per week. The Jivamukti Yoga method developed out of the vibrant creative scene in lower Manhattan, and for decades the New York Jivamukti school was one of the busiest, most popular and most innovative yoga centers in the world. Described as ‚ÄúThe Wild Child of Yoga" by Paper magazine, Jivamukti always attracted highly creative, ambitious and vital students, drawn to the vigorous Hatha Yoga classes and the deeply spiritual sense of community found at the center. Evolving to Three Boons Yoga Berlin allows us to stay local and keeps us independent and true to ourselves, enabling us to continue to embody what we loved about Jivamukti Yoga, once upon a time, when we adopted the name Jivamukti Yoga Berlin: Being hot, hip and holy Wild Children of Yoga, independent of global policies and corporations. name: Abad√° - Capoeira Berlin
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Abad√° - Capoeira Berlin', 'description': 'Capoeira ist eine brasilianische Kampf- kunst bzw. ein Kampftanz, dessen Ursprung auf dem afrikanischen Ni- golo (‚ÄûZebratanz‚Äú) zur√ºckgef√ºhrt wird. Capoeira wurde w√§hrend der Kolonialzeit in Brasilien von aus Afrika verschleppten Sklaven praktiziert und weiter entwickelt. Es wird heutzutage zwischen zwei Hauptrichtungen unter- schieden: dem traditionellen Capoeira Angola und dem modernen Capoeira Regional. Die afrikanischen Elemente verschmolzen in Capoeira Regional im Laufe der Jahre zus√§tzlich mit Einfl√ºssen anderer Kampfk√ºnste, wie z. B. Ringen, Jiu Jitsu und Wushu. Zu dieser Zeit (etwa 1970er Jahre) entwickelten sich auch viele der heute charakteristischen Akrobatiken wie hohe, gedrehte Spr√ºnge oder Salti; auch wenn viele der bodennahen Akrobatiken zumindest in der Tendenz vorhanden waren. Inhaltlich ist Capoeira von drei Ebenen gepr√§gt: dem Kampf, der Musik und der ‚ÄûRoda‚Äú (port. ‚ÄûKreis‚Äú) als gesellschaftlichen Rahmen, in der der Kampf stattfindet. Die Kampftechniken selbst zeichnen sich durch extreme Flexibilit√§t aus; es gibt viele Drehtritte, eingesprungene Tritte und Akrobatik. Traditionell wird zu dem Kampf Musik gespielt. Diese folgt einem Endlos- Rhythmus in verschiedenen Variationen. Dazu werden passende, h√§ufig noch aus der Zeit der Sklaverei stammende, Lieder gesungen. Auf fortgeschrittenem Niveau trainierst du Strategie und Taktik des Freikampfes (Kumite) mit dem Ziel die erlernten Prinzipien im Kampf gegen einen Gegner anzuwenden. name: Three Boons Yoga Kreuzberg ‚Äì f.k.a. Jivamukti Berlin
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Three Boons Yoga Kreuzberg ‚Äì f.k.a. Jivamukti Berlin', 'description': 'Formerly known as Jivamukti Yoga Berlin, Three Boons Yoga Berlin in Mitte and Kreuzberg have been independent Jivamukti Yoga schools since 2009, offering, at (pre-Corona) times, up to 150 yoga classes a week. The vast majority of these classes have been Jivamukti Yoga classes, and the vast majority of our teachers have been Jivamukti Yoga teachers, some of the best-trained and most experienced out there. With our new name, nothing of the above really changes, except for, well, the name: You will still able to access the same high-quality Jivamukti Yoga classes with some of the best and coolest yoga teachers out there. Hopefully, we will see each other again very soon in a yoga class in one of our beautiful studios, which we have been busy renovating and improving massively during the past months. And for the time being, let‚Äôs stay in touch through Three Boons Yoga Online offering more than 50 Live-Stream classes per week. The Jivamukti Yoga method developed out of the vibrant creative scene in lower Manhattan, and for decades the New York Jivamukti school was one of the busiest, most popular and most innovative yoga centers in the world. Described as ‚ÄúThe Wild Child of Yoga" by Paper magazine, Jivamukti always attracted highly creative, ambitious and vital students, drawn to the vigorous Hatha Yoga classes and the deeply spiritual sense of community found at the center. description: Formerly known as Jivamukti Yoga Berlin, Three Boons Yoga Berlin in Mitte and Kreuzberg have been independent Jivamukti Yoga schools since 2009, offering, at (pre-Corona) times, up to 150 yoga classes a week. The vast majority of these classes have been Jivamukti Yoga classes, and the vast majority of our teachers have been Jivamukti Yoga teachers, some of the best-trained and most experienced out there. name: Yoga Futura Neuk√∂lln
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Yoga Futura Neuk√∂lln', 'description': 'At Yoga Futura we are here to support you in establishing or deepening your yoga practice, no matter your circumstances. We believe that a steady and continuous yoga practice can benefit all, and our commitment is finding the approach that fits your individual needs. Founded by two friends, mothers and partners, this space is the manifestation of our love for yoga and community. Aside finding joy in practicing, we believe one of the greatest benefits of yoga is the connection it brings within its practitioners. Having met through yoga, our friendship symbolises the power of this union. When thinking about how we want to ensure that everyone feels welcome and safe to practice in our studio, we identified a few important principles which we have carried over into our teachings. These include placing emphasis on consent as the basis of any physical touch, ensuring that the practice is non-injurious, and fostering an environment where yoga is not synonymous with being able-bodied. The yoga that we practice and teach is not new, it is a result of the evolution that has been occurring within and outside of the yoga tradition for hundreds of years. Our approach however is unique in that it aims to re-evaluate which of these traditions still serves us today. Yoga Futura stands for a sustainable practice that will support you in all the different phases of your life.', 'address': {'@type': 'PostalAddress', 'addressLocality': 'Berlin, Germany', 'addressCountry': 'Germany', 'postalCode': '12059', 'streetAddress': 'Weigandufer 18'}, 'telephone': '', 'geo': {'@type': 'GeoCoordinates', 'latitude': '52.4831013', 'longitude': '13.4471193'}, 'priceRange': '-', 'image': 'https://storage.googleapis.com/download/storage/v1/b/usc-pro-uscweb-live-media/o/de-live%2Foriginal_2048x1152_dc2082d53fe4-ADDB06D3_6989_439A_B963_623DAE743A42_1644852605813520_admin.jpg?generation=1644852605910606&alt=media'}

EN: High On Yoga offers physically and spiritually intense vinyasa yoga to sweat and bring joy. We are a yoga studio embracing the Berlin free spirit and to be an inclusive place to everyone all our courses are in English. Our yoga courses combine dynamic alignment-focused Ashtanga-based flow with an embracing body-positive approach. Each High On Yoga class is a performance introducing the wholeness and complicity of yoga as a method for good life. Expect the sound of harmonium, mantra chanting and a lot of hands-on adjustments and assists. A yoga high is guaranteed.

name: Triathlon Crew Berlin - Kombibad Seestra√üe
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Triathlon Crew Berlin - Kombibad Seestra√üe', 'description': 'Willkommen bei der Triathloncrew Berlin. Der Triathlonsport wird immer mehr zum Volkssport, bietet er doch viele M√∂glichkeiten sich sportlich zu fordern und weiterzuentwickeln. Aber aus welchen Disziplinen besteht der Triathlon? Im TRIATHLON steht als erste Disziplin das SCHWIMMEN an, gefolgt vom RADFAHREN und dem LAUFEN zum Schluss. Drei Disziplinen deren k√∂rperliche Anforderungen sehr verschieden ausfallen k√∂nnen. Entsprechend gibt es unter den Sportlern kaum jemanden der Experte in allen drei Disziplinen ist. Dieses Problem wollen wir von der Triathloncrew Berlin l√∂sen. Mitten in Berlin, Indoor und Outdoor, bieten wir ein sehr technikorientiertes Training aller Disziplinen an. Denn Schwimmen ist nicht gleich Schwimmen und Laufen nicht gleich Laufen. Die meisten unserer Kurse enthalten deshalb viele technische Komponente zur Steigerung der √ñkonomie und Effizienz, mit dem Ziel der Leistungsoptimierung. Dabei achten wir darauf immer auf dem neuesten Stand der wissenschaftlichen Lehrmeinung und Technik zu sein. Neuerungen flie√üen dabei sehr schnell in das Training mit ein. Besonders stolz sind wir darauf Berlins erstes und einziges SMART Rollentrainer-Radtraining anbieten zu k√∂nnen. Mithilfe Ihres eigenen Rades, und Ihrer eigenen individuellen Radeinstellung (auch nach Bikefitting), holen wir das Maximum aus Ihner Leistungsf√§higkeit heraus. Wir bieten folgende Kurse an: Schwimmen: ‚Ä¢tKraultechnik ‚Ä¢tKraulworkout HIT ‚Ä¢tKraultechnik Open Water ‚Ä¢tKraulworkout HIT Open Water ‚Ä¢tBike-Swim-Bike Koppeltraining Open Water Radfahren mit dem eigenen Rad (Shimano Schaltung): ‚Ä¢tSMART Rollentraining Technik ‚Ä¢tSMART Rollentraining VO2max ‚Ä¢tSMART Rollentraining LIT ‚Ä¢tBike-Swim-Bike Koppeltraining ‚Ä¢tLIT Long Bike Ausfahrt Laufen: ‚Ä¢tLauftechnik und -√∂konomietraining ‚Ä¢tHIT & Run ‚Ä¢tTriathloncrew Koppeltraining ‚Ä¢tLIT Long Run Funktionelles Krafttraining: ‚Ä¢tTraining der Triathlonspezifischen Arbeitsmuskulatur ‚Ä¢tCoretraining ‚Ä¢tZugseiltraining Bei den Kursen handelt es sich um ausgesuchte Kurse, die jeweils nach Saison und Trainingsphase in das Training integriert werden k√∂nnen. Neben den Inhalten des Trainings ist eines der wichtigsten Erfolgsfaktoren zur Verbesserung der Leistungsf√§higkeit, die Kontinuit√§t des Trainings. Mit fachlicher Kompetenz, Spa√ü und Enthusiasmus freuen wir uns, Ihnen dabei unter die Arme greifen zu d√ºrfen. English: Welcome to the Triathlon Crew Berlin. Triathlon is becoming an ever more popular sport, since it offers many opportunities to challenge and further develop yourself and your sporting ability. But what disciplines does the triathlon consist of? TRIATHLON consists of SWIMMING, followed by BIKING and RUNNING at the end. Three disciplines whose physical requirements can be very different. Accordingly, there are very few athletes who are expert in all three elements. At the Triathloncrew Berlin, we love to face these challenges and build a supportive training community. Based in the middle of Berlin, with indoor and outdoor facilities, we offer very technology-oriented training in all disciplines. We recognize that swimming, cycling and running performance are built from strength, endurance and technical proficiency. Therefore, most of our courses contain many technical components to increase economy and efficiency, with the aim of optimizing performance. We make sure that we are always up to date with the latest scientific opinions and technology, enabling new innovations to flow quickly into the training. We are particularly proud to be able to offer Berlin's first and only SMART bike training. With the help of your own bike and your own individual bike setting (even after bike fitting), we get the most out of your performance. You may choose to participate in the specific training sessions that suit your needs, enabling tailored support integrated into your existing training program. In addition to the content of the training, one of the most important success factors for improving performance is the continuity of the training. With professional competence, fun and enthusiasm, we look forward to helping you.', 'address': {'@type': 'PostalAddress', 'addressLocality': 'Berlin, Germany', 'addressCountry': 'Germany', 'postalCode': '13347', 'streetAddress': 'Seestra√üe 80'}, 'telephone': '', 'geo': {'@type': 'GeoCoordinates', 'latitude': '52.557347', 'longitude': '13.363945'}, 'priceRange': '-', 'image': 'https://storage.googleapis.com/download/storage/v1/b/usc-pro-uscweb-live-media/o/de-live%2Foriginal_1280x720_657E83FA-00E3-4EB4-87AF-68D2A5093259_1602591971447060_admin.jpeg?alt=media'}

Mit fachlicher Kompetenz, Spa√ü und Enthusiasmus freuen wir uns, Ihnen dabei unter die Arme greifen zu d√ºrfen. English: Welcome to the Triathlon Crew Berlin. Triathlon is becoming an ever more popular sport, since it offers many opportunities to challenge and further develop yourself and your sporting ability. But what disciplines does the triathlon consist of? TRIATHLON consists of SWIMMING, followed by BIKING and RUNNING at the end. Three disciplines whose physical requirements can be very different. Accordingly, there are very few athletes who are expert in all three elements. At the Triathloncrew Berlin, we love to face these challenges and build a supportive training community. Based in the middle of Berlin, with indoor and outdoor facilities, we offer very technology-oriented training in all disciplines. We recognize that swimming, cycling and running performance are built from strength, endurance and technical proficiency. Therefore, most of our courses contain many technical components to increase economy and efficiency, with the aim of optimizing performance. We make sure that we are always up to date with the latest scientific opinions and technology, enabling new innovations to flow quickly into the training. With the help of your own bike and your own individual bike setting (even after bike fitting), we get the most out of your performance. You may choose to participate in the specific training sessions that suit your needs, enabling tailored support integrated into your existing training program. In addition to the content of the training, one of the most important success factors for improving performance is the continuity of the training. With professional competence, fun and enthusiasm, we look forward to helping you.

Die meisten unserer Kurse enthalten deshalb viele technische Komponente zur Steigerung der √ñkonomie und Effizienz, mit dem Ziel der Leistungsoptimierung. Dabei achten wir darauf immer auf dem neuesten Stand der wissenschaftlichen Lehrmeinung und Technik zu sein. Neuerungen flie√üen dabei sehr schnell in das Training mit ein. Besonders stolz sind wir darauf Berlins erstes und einziges SMART Rollentrainer-Radtraining anbieten zu k√∂nnen. Mithilfe Ihres eigenen Rades, und Ihrer eigenen individuellen Radeinstellung (auch nach Bikefitting), holen wir das Maximum aus Ihner Leistungsf√§higkeit heraus. Wir bieten folgende Kurse an: Schwimmen: ‚Ä¢tKraultechnik ‚Ä¢tKraulworkout HIT ‚Ä¢tKraultechnik Open Water ‚Ä¢tKraulworkout HIT Open Water ‚Ä¢tBike-Swim-Bike Koppeltraining Open Water Radfahren mit dem eigenen Rad (Shimano Schaltung): ‚Ä¢tSMART Rollentraining Technik ‚Ä¢tSMART Rollentraining VO2max ‚Ä¢tSMART Rollentraining LIT ‚Ä¢tBike-Swim-Bike Koppeltraining ‚Ä¢tLIT Long Bike Ausfahrt Laufen: ‚Ä¢tLauftechnik und -√∂konomietraining ‚Ä¢tHIT & Run ‚Ä¢tTriathloncrew Koppeltraining ‚Ä¢tLIT Long Run Funktionelles Krafttraining: ‚Ä¢tTraining der Triathlonspezifischen Arbeitsmuskulatur ‚Ä¢tCoretraining ‚Ä¢tZugseiltraining Bei den Kursen handelt es sich um ausgesuchte Kurse, die jeweils nach Saison und Trainingsphase in das Training integriert werden k√∂nnen. Neben den Inhalten des Trainings ist eines der wichtigsten Erfolgsfaktoren zur Verbesserung der Leistungsf√§higkeit, die Kontinuit√§t des Trainings. Mit fachlicher Kompetenz, Spa√ü und Enthusiasmus freuen wir uns, Ihnen dabei unter die Arme greifen zu d√ºrfen. English: Welcome to the Triathlon Crew Berlin. Triathlon is becoming an ever more popular sport, since it offers many opportunities to challenge and further develop yourself and your sporting ability. But what disciplines does the triathlon consist of? TRIATHLON consists of SWIMMING, followed by BIKING and RUNNING at the end. Three disciplines whose physical requirements can be very different. Accordingly, there are very few athletes who are expert in all three elements. At the Triathloncrew Berlin, we love to face these challenges and build a supportive training community. Based in the middle of Berlin, with indoor and outdoor facilities, we offer very technology-oriented training in all disciplines. We recognize that swimming, cycling and running performance are built from strength, endurance and technical proficiency. Therefore, most of our courses contain many technical components to increase economy and efficiency, with the aim of optimizing performance. We make sure that we are always up to date with the latest scientific opinions and technology, enabling new innovations to flow quickly into the training. We are particularly proud to be able to offer Berlin's first and only SMART bike training. With the help of your own bike and your own individual bike setting (even after bike fitting), we get the most out of your performance. You may choose to participate in the specific training sessions that suit your needs, enabling tailored support integrated into your existing training program. In addition to the content of the training, one of the most important success factors for improving performance is the continuity of the training. With professional competence, fun and enthusiasm, we look forward to helping you.

name: Three Boons Yoga Berlin Charlottenburg
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Three Boons Yoga Berlin Charlottenburg', 'description': 'Formerly known as Jivamukti Yoga Berlin, Three Boons Yoga Berlin in Mitte and Kreuzberg have been independent Jivamukti Yoga schools since 2009, offering, at (pre-Corona) times, up to 150 yoga classes a week. The vast majority of these classes have been Jivamukti Yoga classes, and the vast majority of our teachers have been Jivamukti Yoga teachers, some of the best-trained and most experienced out there. With our new name, nothing of the above really changes, except for, well, the name: You will still able to access the same high-quality Jivamukti Yoga classes with some of the best and coolest yoga teachers out there. Hopefully, we will see each other again very soon in a yoga class in one of our beautiful studios, which we have been busy renovating and improving massively during the past months. And for the time being, let‚Äôs stay in touch through Three Boons Yoga Online offering more than 50 Live-Stream classes per week. The Jivamukti Yoga method developed out of the vibrant creative scene in lower Manhattan, and for decades the New York Jivamukti school was one of the busiest, most popular and most innovative yoga centers in the world. Described as ‚ÄúThe Wild Child of Yoga" by Paper magazine, Jivamukti always attracted highly creative, ambitious and vital students, drawn to the vigorous Hatha Yoga classes and the deeply spiritual sense of community found at the center. Evolving to Three Boons Yoga Berlin allows us to stay local and keeps us independent and true to ourselves, enabling us to continue to embody what we loved about Jivamukti Yoga, once upon a time, when we adopted the name Jivamukti Yoga Berlin: Being hot, hip and holy Wild Children of Yoga, independent of global policies and corporations. Accordingly, there are very few athletes who are expert in all three elements. At the Triathloncrew Berlin, we love to face these challenges and build a supportive training community. Based in the middle of Berlin, with indoor and outdoor facilities, we offer very technology-oriented training in all disciplines. We recognize that swimming, cycling and running performance are built from strength, endurance and technical proficiency. Therefore, most of our courses contain many technical components to increase economy and efficiency, with the aim of optimizing performance. We make sure that we are always up to date with the latest scientific opinions and technology, enabling new innovations to flow quickly into the training. We are particularly proud to be able to offer Berlin's first and only SMART bike training. With the help of your own bike and your own individual bike setting (even after bike fitting), we get the most out of your performance. You may choose to participate in the specific training sessions that suit your needs, enabling tailored support integrated into your existing training program. In addition to the content of the training, one of the most important success factors for improving performance is the continuity of the training. metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Rocket Station', 'description': 'Our vision is to create a space where people can connect. Not only rolling out the mat next to each other, but to share the experience that happens on that mat and share a cup of tea after the class. Where experienced yogis meet newbies, the calm ones the restless ones, and they all find something that makes them want to return to the station. We believe in developing together. This beautiful place offers you challenges, inspiration, and different perspectives. At the Rocket Station you can find a wide range of classes, events not only to meet others but also to discover different sides of yourself. We got your back if you have never seen a yoga mat before, and we kick your butt if you are on the mat twice a day. A place where we invite you all to land. If you are here, BE here! Dieser wunderbare Ort bietet euch Herausforderungen, Inspiration und neue Perspektiven. name: Massage With Simon
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Massage With Simon', 'description': 'The two types of massage I do are sports/deep tissue and relaxation/classical. I have been working as a massage therapist since 2014, in gyms, spas and as a freelancer. I studied Remedial Massage and Relaxation Massage in Australia. I have a Bachelor of Science, and a Grad Dip in Psychology. Before each session, we do a quick check in, to see what areas you would like to have worked on, and what level of physical intensity you would like for today. During the session, I will check in to see that the pressure is the right amount for you. You may talk as little or as much as you like, for me I don‚Äôt mind what our conversation level is. I will mirror you, as this helps to create an experience that matches your needs. How does massage work? The most likely specific mechanism of how massage works is through touch, with strength of intensity being an individual preference. Massage has strong benefits for mental health (anxiety/depression), which supports its use as wellness, and as part of broader approach to looking after oneself.', 'address': {'@type': 'PostalAddress', 'addressLocality': 'Berlin, Germany', 'addressCountry': 'Germany', 'postalCode': '12049', 'streetAddress': 'Mahlowerstr 5'}, 'telephone': '', 'geo': {'@type': 'GeoCoordinates', 'latitude': '52.4800766', 'longitude': '13.4237456'}, 'priceRange': '-', 'image': 'https://storage.googleapis.com/download/storage/v1/b/usc-pro-uscweb-live-media/o/de-live%2Foriginal_6240x3510_03_MG_7322Edit1_1694513125338554_admin.jpg?generation=1694513125469830&alt=media'}

name: Yoga Futura Kreuzberg
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Yoga Futura Kreuzberg', 'description': 'At Yoga Futura we are here to support you in establishing or deepening your yoga practice, no matter your circumstances. We believe that a steady and continuous yoga practice can benefit all, and our commitment is finding the approach that fits your individual needs. Founded by two friends, mothers and partners, this space is the manifestation of our love for yoga and community. Aside finding joy in practicing, we believe one of the greatest benefits of yoga is the connection it brings within its practitioners. Having met through yoga, our friendship symbolises the power of this union. When thinking about how we want to ensure that everyone feels welcome and safe to practice in our studio, we identified a few important principles which we have carried over into our teachings. These include placing emphasis on consent as the basis of any physical touch, ensuring that the practice is non-injurious, and fostering an environment where yoga is not synonymous with being able-bodied. The yoga that we practice and teach is not new, it is a result of the evolution that has been occurring within and outside of the yoga tradition for hundreds of years. Our approach however is unique in that it aims to re-evaluate which of these traditions still serves us today. Yoga Futura stands for a sustainable practice that will support you in all the different phases of your life.', 'address': {'@type': 'PostalAddress', 'addressLocality': 'Berlin, Germany', 'addressCountry': 'Germany', 'postalCode': '10965', 'streetAddress': 'Kreuzbergstrasse 30'}, 'telephone': '', 'geo': {'@type': 'GeoCoordinates', 'latitude': '52.4902944', 'longitude': '13.3777416'}, 'priceRange': '-', 'image': 'https://storage.googleapis.com/download/storage/v1/b/usc-pro-uscweb-live-media/o/de-live%2Foriginal_1024x576_de-live_venueHome_1024x576_86ec5cb52ec8-AAFA09EB_A9B0_4F45_9BA9_99EB4F367D69_1644852610349229_admin_170003430549563_admin.jpg?generation=1700034305115972&alt=media'}
description: At Yoga Futura we are here to support you in establishing or deepening your yoga practice, no matter your circumstances. We believe that a steady and continuous yoga practice can benefit all, and our commitment is finding the approach that fits your individual needs. Founded by two friends, mothers and partners, this space is the manifestation of our love for yoga and community. Aside finding joy in practicing, we believe one of the greatest benefits of yoga is the connection it brings within its practitioners. Having met through yoga, our friendship symbolises the power of this union. When thinking about how we want to ensure that everyone feels welcome and safe to practice in our studio, we identified a few important principles which we have carried over into our teachings. These include placing emphasis on consent as the basis of any physical touch, ensuring that the practice is non-injurious, and fostering an environment where yoga is not synonymous with being able-bodied. The yoga that we practice and teach is not new, it is a result of the evolution that has been occurring within and outside of the yoga tradition for hundreds of years. Our approach however is unique in that it aims to re-evaluate which of these traditions still serves us today. Yoga Futura stands for a sustainable practice that will support you in all the different phases of your life.

Yoga in Berlin Prenzlauer Berg KALAA Yoga Berlin is a yoga school in Prenzlauer Berg, next to Helmholzplatz. Our studio is located in the back house of a historical Berlin building, in a former printing company with a view into the greenery. Since 2011 we have been filling the space with movement, a warm community and the passion for yoga. During the warmer months some of the classes take place at our big and quiet yoga garden. Our teachers have accomplished qualified yoga trainings. name: Kizomba mit Kizombaberlin.de - indoor
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Kizomba mit Kizombaberlin.de - indoor', 'description': 'I was born on a small island in Brazil and inspired by my uncle I wanted to dance like Michael Jackson. From Brazilian rhythms to Salsa, Bachata and Tango, I came to Kizomba. Often accompanied by music in my native language, Kizomba won me over very quickly. Because of the cultural closeness to my home country, where it is very much about the feeling with the music and having fun while dancing. It is very close to my heart to convey this (life) feeling to the students, so that they can absorb it for themselves and combine it with their very own melody. So that from clean- easily usable on the dance floor- figures and the interpretation of music above all a feeling is conveyed to the partner. All of this whilst my sport scientist background enables me to have a deeply didactic approach. No matter whether dancing or teaching, my dream is to still dance, teach and meet you on the dance floors until I am a grandfather. Until then, I invite you to my classes to meet new people and to be inspired by my experiences & my positive nature. I am looking forward to meeting you. Felipe', 'address': {'@type': 'PostalAddress', 'addressLocality': 'Berlin, Germany', 'addressCountry': 'Germany', 'postalCode': '10179', 'streetAddress': 'Inselstra√üe 9'}, 'telephone': '', 'geo': {'@type': 'GeoCoordinates', 'latitude': '52.5122591', 'longitude': '13.4118726'}, 'priceRange': '-', 'image': 'https://storage.googleapis.com/download/storage/v1/b/usc-pro-uscweb-live-media/o/de-live%2Foriginal_1125x633_9a5481caab7d-27F511FB_F648_415A_B725_BC8934B2D4A6_1657785499159017_admin.png?generation=1657785499222759&alt=media'}
description: I was born on a small island in Brazil and inspired by my uncle I wanted to dance like Michael Jackson. From Brazilian rhythms to Salsa, Bachata and Tango, I came to Kizomba. Often accompanied by music in my native language, Kizomba won me over very quickly. Because of the cultural closeness to my home country, where it is very much about the feeling with the music and having fun while dancing. It is very close to my heart to convey this (life) feeling to the students, so that they can absorb it for themselves and combine it with their very own melody. So that from clean- easily usable on the dance floor- figures and the interpretation of music above all a feeling is conveyed to the partner. All of this whilst my sport scientist background enables me to have a deeply didactic approach. No matter whether dancing or teaching, my dream is to still dance, teach and meet you on the dance floors until I am a grandfather. Until then, I invite you to my classes to meet new people and to be inspired by my experiences & my positive nature. I am looking forward to meeting you. Felipe

Our yoga courses combine dynamic alignment-focused Ashtanga-based flow with an embracing body-positive approach. Each High On Yoga class is a performance introducing the wholeness and complicity of yoga as a method for good life. Expect the sound of harmonium, mantra chanting and a lot of hands-on adjustments and assists. A yoga high is guaranteed.

name: Somatische Akademie Berlin
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Somatische Akademie Berlin', 'description': 'The resonant body. Body-voice work training and movement research This training is based on improvisation, physical theater training, butoh dance practices, and somatic bodywork. Through a guided, animated warm-up, individual and partner improvisations, the aim of this training is to let our body grow towards unknown physical/ mind/ spirit states. It proposes both physical and vocal work focused on the connection between movement and breathing, the work with the energy, and our time-space awareness. Bringing more consciousness to our body-mind allows us to get out of our daily habits and facilitate access to our creativity in a more fluid and generous way. In addition, we will explore the relationship between movement and imagery. The imagery is understood as inner space that can emerge on the surface as a physical event that transforms us today and now. Open to performers, dancers, actors, and anyone interested in creative body research.', 'address': {'@type': 'PostalAddress', 'addressLocality': 'Berlin, Germany', 'addressCountry': 'Germany', 'postalCode': '10999', 'streetAddress': 'Paull-Linker-Ufer 30'}, 'telephone': '', 'geo': {'@type': 'GeoCoordinates', 'latitude': '50.9446145', 'longitude': '6.9456868'}, 'priceRange': '-', 'image': 'https://storage.googleapis.com/download/storage/v1/b/usc-pro-uscweb-live-media/o/de-live%2Foriginal_7534x4238_aa4cb9e5a39e-2024.01.29_Resonantboday_logo_FINAL_Mesa_de_trabajo_1_copia_11_1713169945662278_admin.png?generation=1713169945758515&alt=media'}
description: The resonant body. Body-voice work training and movement research This training is based on improvisation, physical theater training, butoh dance practices, and somatic bodywork. Through a guided, animated warm-up, individual and partner improvisations, the aim of this training is to let our body grow towards unknown physical/ mind/ spirit states. It proposes both physical and vocal work focused on the connection between movement and breathing, the work with the energy, and our time-space awareness. Bringing more consciousness to our body-mind allows us to get out of our daily habits and facilitate access to our creativity in a more fluid and generous way. In addition, we will explore the relationship between movement and imagery. The imagery is understood as inner space that can emerge on the surface as a physical event that transforms us today and now. Open to performers, dancers, actors, and anyone interested in creative body research.

name: Kostis Spyrou - Dance
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Kostis Spyrou - Dance', 'description': 'Kostis Spyrou (b. Athens, Greece, 1989) is a Berlin-based dancer and educator focussed on the human body and its potential as a means of communication and expression. Kostis trained at the KSOT and AKTINA professional contemporary dance training programs in Athens, Greece, where he studied performance, technique, pedagogy, and choreography. Subsequently, he has supplemented his movement knowledge through parkour, acrobatics, and floor-barre as well as through strength, flexibility, and conditioning training. Since 2016, he has been working in Germany as both a professional dance artist and as an instructor in university, dance school, and studio contexts. Kostis offers regular classes and workshops at multiple venues in Berlin. Intentionally focussed on specific themes and key ideas, the classes are suitable for beginner, intermediate and advanced movers and designed to challenge, motivate, and educate. metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Ashtanga Yoga Berlin', 'description': 'Ashtanga Yoga Berlin (since 2004) is the place for eager Yoga practitioners who seek guidance and precise support in the advanced and subtle Yoga practices. Ashtanga is a non-esoteric, straightforward practice method, deeply rooted in the mind-blowing yogic scriptures. Come if you are ready to practice Yoga every day so you can develop your personal advanced Yoga practice. Go beyond the mainstream! Call us: +493048496665. === WHAT IS ASHTANGA YOGA MYSORE STYLE? === Mysore Style is the classical Indian Yoga teaching method. Individual tuition in small groups (10 ‚Äì 20 practitioners) allows for cultivating an individual practice and ‚Äúinward-orientation‚Äù (pratyak-cetana) of your mind. The result is the exact opposite of the wide-spread (western) approach of ‚Äúteacher-imitation‚Äù, which directs your awareness outwards and puffs up the ego. True yogic experiences cannot arise if you look away from the self. Try the difference and you‚Äôll understand. === HOW CAN YOU LEARN MYSORE STYLE? === After a month of Mysore Style practice you will have escaped the boredom of flowery platitudes of copy-paste Yoga. But be warned: True Yoga needs method and dedication. Ashtanga is constructed to be challenging for your body, nervous system and ego structure. It‚Äôs all quite natural, just give us a call and we explain the details: +49.30.48496665. === YOU HAVE AN ASHTANGA PRACTICE? GO BEYOND! === If you know what you are doing you can simply join our Mysore classes any time. You will discover fascinating internal alignment tools which remove all major obstacles on your path with ease. Learn why mulabandha is not what you think and experience the true meaning of ‚Äúadvanced‚Äù in Yoga. === YOGA INJURIES? WHAT‚ÄôS THAT?!? === ‚ÄúAsana practice is (...) not which ruins someone‚Äôs health‚Äù - Adi Shankara, ca. 8th cent. CE. Both cause and solution for Shankara‚Äôs observation have not changed over the past 1200 years. Yoga injuries come from incorrect practice. Incorrect practice comes from incorrect teaching. Incorrect teaching is ignorantly serving the ego rather than the self. Injuries disappear when you stop re-injuring yourself. Your body heals within days when the cause of an injury is removed. That‚Äôs your inherent nature. It is that simple. We will help you. === THE MEANING OF YOGA === The process of Yoga is a fundamental transformation of how you perceive the world and your own self. The only valid map on that path are the ancient yogic scriptures such as Yoga Sutra, the Bhagavad Gita etc. This is our foundation, even if it looks like a physical practice. === BECOME PART OF OUR COMMUNITY === It is an important goal for us to build a community of practitioners from all yoga traditions. name: Berlin Handstand School
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Berlin Handstand School', 'description': 'Luka is a mover that hasn't stopped moving since he left his IT chair some years ago. He is a bubble of ideas; about life, Acroyoga, and massage/bodywork. Very rarely a day passes without some kind of movement practice or community / teaching events. Luka has been teaching the past years around the world with a yearly 3 month stay in Japan and also South America and Europe. With the organisation Japanero.pro he organises events ranging from yoga, Acroyoga, partner acrobatics, handstands, massage and running - usually always in beautiful nature places around Europe. Originally from Croatia he has now settled in Berlin and is starting with regular weekly classes in different movement areas. name: Ori Tahiti @ Atelier De La Danse
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Ori Tahiti @ Atelier De La Danse', 'description': 'Polynesische T√§nze beinhalten viel mehr als nur sch√∂ne Bewegungen zu harmonischer oder temperamentvoller Musik. Te Ora bedeutet auf tahitianisch das Leben. Es geht um Geschichten des Lebens wie Liebe, besondere Begebenheiten oder die Natur. Man entwickelt hierbei auch einen entspannten Lebensstil im Geiste von Aloha, in Harmonie mit der Natur und den Menschen um uns herum bzw. mit uns selbst. Es geht um eine ganze Kultur und, indem wir tiefer in sie hinein tauchen durch den Tanz, verbinden wir uns tiefer mit ihr und bringen diesen Geist in unser gesamtes Leben ein. Andrea Claassen-Hansen ist ausgebildete B√ºhnent√§nzerin und hat 4 Lehrertrainings der Te Tuamarama International School of Tahitian Dance unter der Leitung von Joelle Berg (Conservatoire de Papeete) absolviert. Sie unterrichtet seit 2015 in dieser Lineage. Auch hat sie Kurse und Workshops im Rahmen der TU Hochschulsport Sektion Tanz abgehalten. Andrea unterrichtet in Berlin w√∂chentliche Kurse in Ori Tahiti Anf√§nger Online (Donnerstag) und Ori Tahiti Anf√§nger vor Ort im Studio (Sonntags) Polynesian dances contain much more than just beautiful movements to harmonious or spirited music. Te Ora means life in Tahitian. It is about stories of life like love, special events or nature. One also develops a relaxed lifestyle in the spirit of Aloha, in harmony with nature and the people around us or with ourselves. It is about a whole culture and, by diving deeper into it through dance, we connect more deeply with it and bring this spirit into our whole life. Andrea Claassen-Hansen is a trained stage dancer and has completed 4 teacher training courses at Te Tuamarama International School of Tahitian Dance under the direction of Joelle Berg (Conservatoire de Papeete). She has been teaching in this lineage since 2015. She has also held courses and workshops within the TU Hochschulsport Sektion Tanz. name: Berlin Contemporary Dance - ADA studio
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Berlin Contemporary Dance - ADA studio', 'description': 'Iliana's workshops are emphasizing on Contemporary Dance technique buildup and Improvisation. The focus is on floor work practice, organic movement, fluidity and awareness. Technique is approached as a guide to efficiency in the movement of the human body. The internal structure of the class is made to gradually deepen in the technique and develop through it. The main elements studied are: -Floor Work: How it works. Developing our relation to the floor through all movement levels, using multiple floor-work patterns and phrases. Using levers and clear pathways, building up a vocabulary that can be used in further understanding the mechanics of movement. From basic floor- patterns to advanced, complicated ones, floor acrobatics, handstands, coordinations. -Dynamics of movement. Flow and organic movement. Study and use of weight, momentum, impulse, swing and flow of movement, developing the body's kinetic intelligence. How grounding works, how to stay connected to the floor through the study of body structure (bones and joints), of weight and use of breath. Organic movement and its impact to the body, use of own body structure in the most efficient way. -Connectivity practice. Spacial and body awareness. Connectivity is studied both in terms of a fully connected moving body and of a mover in a state of full connection with his/her environment. How the body moves in its full awareness, connecting and interacting with its environment - the other people, the space, the floor- and its own inner state at the same time. Spatial and body awareness, together with connectivity practice, helps to develop a unified physical and mental consciousness, thus a moving body in its full consciousness expressing itself in space and time. Throughout the class fixed phrases and exercises are given, practicing the aforementioned elements. The material is highly physical and classes often end up on a longer phrase practice, built from the accumulation of smaller exercises, working also on physical strength, stamina and memory.', 'address': {'@type': 'PostalAddress', 'addressLocality': 'Berlin, Germany', 'addressCountry': 'Germany', 'postalCode': '13357', 'streetAddress': 'Badstr. 41a'}, 'telephone': '', 'geo': {'@type': 'GeoCoordinates', 'latitude': '52.5533873', 'longitude': '13.3772948'}, 'priceRange': '-', 'image': 'https://storage.googleapis.com/download/storage/v1/b/usc-pro-uscweb-live-media/o/de-live%2Foriginal_1879x1057_2a0811651c69-sundaysolos_photo_Andi_Weiland_112__2__16911631329392_admin.jpg?generation=1691163132078457&alt=media'}
description: Iliana's workshops are emphasizing on Contemporary Dance technique buildup and Improvisation. The focus is on floor work practice, organic movement, fluidity and awareness. Technique is approached as a guide to efficiency in the movement of the human body. The internal structure of the class is made to gradually deepen in the technique and develop through it. The main elements studied are: -Floor Work: How it works. Developing our relation to the floor through all movement levels, using multiple floor-work patterns and phrases. Using levers and clear pathways, building up a vocabulary that can be used in further understanding the mechanics of movement. From basic floor- patterns to advanced, complicated ones, floor acrobatics, handstands, coordinations. -Dynamics of movement. Flow and organic movement. Study and use of weight, momentum, impulse, swing and flow of movement, developing the body's kinetic intelligence. How grounding works, how to stay connected to the floor through the study of body structure (bones and joints), of weight and use of breath. Organic movement and its impact to the body, use of own body structure in the most efficient way. -Connectivity practice. Spacial and body awareness. Connectivity is studied both in terms of a fully connected moving body and of a mover in a state of full connection with his/her environment. How the body moves in its full awareness, connecting and interacting with its environment - the other people, the space, the floor- and its own inner state at the same time. Spatial and body awareness, together with connectivity practice, helps to develop a unified physical and mental consciousness, thus a moving body in its full consciousness expressing itself in space and time. Throughout the class fixed phrases and exercises are given, practicing the aforementioned elements. The material is highly physical and classes often end up on a longer phrase practice, built from the accumulation of smaller exercises, working also on physical strength, stamina and memory.

name: Merav Pilates - Heile Haus
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Merav Pilates - Heile Haus', 'description': 'Pilates with Merav Ben Dor. Coming from a background of dance and Yoga, I fell in love with Pilates as it helped me understand my body better, improved my dancing techniques and made me stronger and longer (and if not by actual centimeters, than at least by feeling). Not any less important- Pilates helped me regaining strength after the births of my three kids. Teaching Pilates for the last 7 years increased my appreciation both of the human body and its capabilities, and of the method itself. I have witnessed bodies change through and with the help of Pilates and believe that sometimes our body is wiser than our head, and we should just follow it to its full potential. The classes suit all levels and are putting an emphasis on the connection between breathing and moving, as well as researching the work of the body as a "whole made of separate parts". Hope to see you!', 'address': {'@type': 'PostalAddress', 'addressLocality': 'Berlin, Germany', 'addressCountry': 'Germany', 'postalCode': '10999', 'streetAddress': 'Waldemarstr. 36'}, 'telephone': '+49 1573 0761074', 'geo': {'@type': 'GeoCoordinates', 'latitude': '52.5035082', 'longitude': '13.4191845'}, 'priceRange': '-', 'image': 'https://storage.googleapis.com/download/storage/v1/b/usc-pro-uscweb-live-media/o/de-live%2Foriginal_2448x1377_merav_1583424265762472_admin.jpg?alt=media'}
description: Pilates with Merav Ben Dor. Coming from a background of dance and Yoga, I fell in love with Pilates as it helped me understand my body better, improved my dancing techniques and made me stronger and longer (and if not by actual centimeters, than at least by feeling). Not any less important- Pilates helped me regaining strength after the births of my three kids. Teaching Pilates for the last 7 years increased my appreciation both of the human body and its capabilities, and of the method itself. I have witnessed bodies change through and with the help of Pilates and believe that sometimes our body is wiser than our head, and we should just follow it to its full potential. The classes suit all levels and are putting an emphasis on the connection between breathing and moving, as well as researching the work of the body as a "whole made of separate parts". Hope to see you!

name: ZBK Studio
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'ZBK Studio', 'description': 'The resonant body. Body-voice work training and movement research This training is based on improvisation, physical theater training, butoh dance practices, and somatic bodywork. Through a guided, animated warm-up, individual and partner improvisations, the aim of this training is to let our body grow towards unknown physical/ mind/ spirit states. It proposes both physical and vocal work focused on the connection between movement and breathing, the work with the energy, and our time-space awareness. Bringing more consciousness to our body-mind allows us to get out of our daily habits and facilitate access to our creativity in a more fluid and generous way. In addition, we will explore the relationship between movement and imagery. The imagery is understood as inner space that can emerge on the surface as a physical event that transforms us today and now. Open to performers, dancers, actors, and anyone interested in creative body research.', 'address': {'@type': 'PostalAddress', 'addressLocality': 'Berlin, Germany', 'addressCountry': 'Germany', 'postalCode': '12045', 'streetAddress': 'Weichselstra√üe 34'}, 'telephone': '', 'geo': {'@type': 'GeoCoordinates', 'latitude': '52.4889994', 'longitude': '13.4386589'}, 'priceRange': '-', 'image': 'https://storage.googleapis.com/download/storage/v1/b/usc-pro-uscweb-live-media/o/de-live%2Foriginal_3569x2008_b69c94d4f596-variante4klein_1639658790387341_admin.jpg?generation=1639658790526923&alt=media'}

name: Ashtanga Yoga Zentral
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Ashtanga Yoga Zentral', 'description': 'Ashtanga Yoga is an intensive Hatha Yoga practice with a focus on strength, stamina and flexibility. The traditional system is renowned for its Vinyasa method. This method of Yoga involves synchronising the breath with movement and positions, a process producing internal heat and a purifying sweat that detoxifies muscles and organs. Ashtanga Yoga is a moving meditation, resulting in improved circulation, a light and strong body, and a calm mind. Mysore-Style (named after the south-Indian city where it originated) is the traditional method in which Ashtanga Yoga is learned and practiced. Students receive individualised instruction within a group setting. A series of positions are taught in a specified order, progressing as the student is ready. With consistent, regular practice, the student can truly reap the benefits of Ashtanga yoga, bringing about the union of body and mind, one of the ultimate goals of yoga. Classes take place in the mornings and are open to all levels of practitioner, including those completely new to yoga.', 'address': {'@type': 'PostalAddress', 'addressLocality': 'Berlin, Germany', 'addressCountry': 'Germany', 'postalCode': '10115', 'streetAddress': 'Grosse Hamburger Str. 19A'}, 'telephone': '', 'geo': {'@type': 'GeoCoordinates', 'latitude': '52.5244355', 'longitude': '13.3988557'}, 'priceRange': '-', 'image': 'https://storage.googleapis.com/download/storage/v1/b/usc-pro-uscweb-live-media/o/de-live%2Foriginal_1587x893_96345786363b-IMG_6146bb_1704871595538366_admin.jpg?generation=1704871595749486&alt=media'}
description: Ashtanga Yoga is an intensive Hatha Yoga practice with a focus on strength, stamina and flexibility. The traditional system is renowned for its Vinyasa method. Ashtanga Yoga is a moving meditation, resulting in improved circulation, a light and strong body, and a calm mind. Mysore-Style (named after the south-Indian city where it originated) is the traditional method in which Ashtanga Yoga is learned and practiced. name: Berlin Contemporary Dance - Studio SoniC
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Berlin Contemporary Dance - Studio SoniC', 'description': 'Iliana's workshops are emphasizing on Contemporary Dance technique buildup and Improvisation. The focus is on floor work practice, organic movement, fluidity and awareness. Technique is approached as a guide to efficiency in the movement of the human body. The internal structure of the class is made to gradually deepen in the technique and develop through it. The main elements studied are: -Floor Work: How it works. Developing our relation to the floor through all movement levels, using multiple floor-work patterns and phrases. Using levers and clear pathways, building up a vocabulary that can be used in further understanding the mechanics of movement. From basic floor- patterns to advanced, complicated ones, floor acrobatics, handstands, coordinations. -Dynamics of movement. Flow and organic movement. Study and use of weight, momentum, impulse, swing and flow of movement, developing the body's kinetic intelligence. How grounding works, how to stay connected to the floor through the study of body structure (bones and joints), of weight and use of breath. Organic movement and its impact to the body, use of own body structure in the most efficient way. -Connectivity practice. Spacial and body awareness. Connectivity is studied both in terms of a fully connected moving body and of a mover in a state of full connection with his/her environment. How the body moves in its full awareness, connecting and interacting with its environment - the other people, the space, the floor- and its own inner state at the same time. Spatial and body awareness, together with connectivity practice, helps to develop a unified physical and mental consciousness, thus a moving body in its full consciousness expressing itself in space and time. Throughout the class fixed phrases and exercises are given, practicing the aforementioned elements. The material is highly physical and classes often end up on a longer phrase practice, built from the accumulation of smaller exercises, working also on physical strength, stamina and memory.', 'address': {'@type': 'PostalAddress', 'addressLocality': 'Berlin, Germany', 'addressCountry': 'Germany', 'postalCode': '10999', 'streetAddress': 'Reichenberger Str 124 | 2. Hof, Haus C'}, 'telephone': '', 'geo': {'@type': 'GeoCoordinates', 'latitude': '52.4959286', 'longitude': '13.4317373'}, 'priceRange': '-', 'image': 'https://storage.googleapis.com/download/storage/v1/b/usc-pro-uscweb-live-media/o/de-live%2Foriginal_1879x1057_2c8071d5693a-sundaysolos_photo_Andi_Weiland_112__2_%20(1)_1699609482327496_admin.jpg?generation=1699609482420138&alt=media'}
description: Iliana's workshops are emphasizing on Contemporary Dance technique buildup and Improvisation. The focus is on floor work practice, organic movement, fluidity and awareness. Technique is approached as a guide to efficiency in the movement of the human body. The internal structure of the class is made to gradually deepen in the technique and develop through it. The main elements studied are: -Floor Work: How it works. Developing our relation to the floor through all movement levels, using multiple floor-work patterns and phrases. Using levers and clear pathways, building up a vocabulary that can be used in further understanding the mechanics of movement. From basic floor- patterns to advanced, complicated ones, floor acrobatics, handstands, coordinations. -Dynamics of movement. Flow and organic movement. Study and use of weight, momentum, impulse, swing and flow of movement, developing the body's kinetic intelligence. How grounding works, how to stay connected to the floor through the study of body structure (bones and joints), of weight and use of breath. Organic movement and its impact to the body, use of own body structure in the most efficient way. -Connectivity practice. Spacial and body awareness. Connectivity is studied both in terms of a fully connected moving body and of a mover in a state of full connection with his/her environment. How the body moves in its full awareness, connecting and interacting with its environment - the other people, the space, the floor- and its own inner state at the same time. Spatial and body awareness, together with connectivity practice, helps to develop a unified physical and mental consciousness, thus a moving body in its full consciousness expressing itself in space and time. Throughout the class fixed phrases and exercises are given, practicing the aforementioned elements. The material is highly physical and classes often end up on a longer phrase practice, built from the accumulation of smaller exercises, working also on physical strength, stamina and memory.

name: English Yoga Julie Blumenthal
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'English Yoga Julie Blumenthal', 'description': 'Julie Blumenthal is a Yogiraj (master teacher) in the ISHTA lineage, combining asana and breathwork with accessible tools like subtle body work (mantra, chakras, energy lines etc), inspiring nondualistic philosophy, and Ayurveda. ISHTA practice adapts to each yogi‚Äôs own needs and supports them to find the practice that suits them, with humor and ease. Julie teaches in a cozy, personalized environment that will support you to heat up, chill out, tune in, and learn a little more about yoga, your practice, your body, and yourself in a non-dogmatic, non-judgmental and inspiring way. She believes we do not have to become better or different to experience yoga; we just have to use the tools of body, breath and attention to reconnect to ourselves and restore the balance, inspiration and support we need to move more easily through our lives. Classes focus on a physical, philosophical or energetic theme that changes week to week. All classes offer a well-rounded asana practice and include elements of meditation and relaxation, as well as some challenges, and lots of personal attention. Modifications and variations are always offered to help you find the ideal practice for you on any given day. Mats and props are all available for use. A teacher of teachers, she leads workshops and Level 1 and Level 2 Yoga Alliance teacher trainings in the ISHTA style in Berlin in addition to her weekly classes. She is known for her wise sequencing, her sense of humor, her ability to make anatomy and philosophy fun and accessible to her students, and her soothing chanting at the end of class. For more about Julie, visit www.julieblumenthal.com. metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Salzhain - Salz Yoga', 'description': 'Imagine yourself in a saltroom surrounded by 14 tons of salt in the middle of the city, yet far away from it all. We offer 45 minute Salt Sessions throughout the week at various times of the morning, day, and night for guests seeking a short break from the stress of life. Come experience a mini-vacay without ever leaving the city. You'll understand better what we mean when you enjoy a session with us. We also offer a variety of courses/classes and workshops for those wanting to elevate their experience in the saltroom. Different Yoga classes and courses are offered in the saltroom with the saltair inhalation. name: Berlin Contemporary Dance - Studio2
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Berlin Contemporary Dance - Studio2', 'description': 'Iliana's workshops are emphasizing on Contemporary Dance technique buildup and Improvisation. The focus is on floor work practice, organic movement, fluidity and awareness. Technique is approached as a guide to efficiency in the movement of the human body. The internal structure of the class is made to gradually deepen in the technique and develop through it. The main elements studied are: -Floor Work: How it works. Developing our relation to the floor through all movement levels, using multiple floor-work patterns and phrases. Using levers and clear pathways, building up a vocabulary that can be used in further understanding the mechanics of movement. From basic floor- patterns to advanced, complicated ones, floor acrobatics, handstands, coordinations. -Dynamics of movement. Flow and organic movement. Study and use of weight, momentum, impulse, swing and flow of movement, developing the body's kinetic intelligence. How grounding works, how to stay connected to the floor through the study of body structure (bones and joints), of weight and use of breath. Organic movement and its impact to the body, use of own body structure in the most efficient way. -Connectivity practice. Spacial and body awareness. Connectivity is studied both in terms of a fully connected moving body and of a mover in a state of full connection with his/her environment. How the body moves in its full awareness, connecting and interacting with its environment - the other people, the space, the floor- and its own inner state at the same time. Spatial and body awareness, together with connectivity practice, helps to develop a unified physical and mental consciousness, thus a moving body in its full consciousness expressing itself in space and time. Throughout the class fixed phrases and exercises are given, practicing the aforementioned elements. The material is highly physical and classes often end up on a longer phrase practice, built from the accumulation of smaller exercises, working also on physical strength, stamina and memory.', 'address': {'@type': 'PostalAddress', 'addressLocality': 'Berlin, Germany', 'addressCountry': 'Germany', 'postalCode': '10997', 'streetAddress': 'Mariannenpl. 2'}, 'telephone': '', 'geo': {'@type': 'GeoCoordinates', 'latitude': '52.5038945', 'longitude': '13.4240746'}, 'priceRange': '-', 'image': 'https://storage.googleapis.com/download/storage/v1/b/usc-pro-uscweb-live-media/o/de-live%2Foriginal_2048x1152_733963a385fe-105_1680785971671200_admin.jpg?generation=1680785971748887&alt=media'}
description: Iliana's workshops are emphasizing on Contemporary Dance technique buildup and Improvisation. The focus is on floor work practice, organic movement, fluidity and awareness. Technique is approached as a guide to efficiency in the movement of the human body. The internal structure of the class is made to gradually deepen in the technique and develop through it. The main elements studied are: -Floor Work: How it works. Developing our relation to the floor through all movement levels, using multiple floor-work patterns and phrases. Using levers and clear pathways, building up a vocabulary that can be used in further understanding the mechanics of movement. From basic floor- patterns to advanced, complicated ones, floor acrobatics, handstands, coordinations. -Dynamics of movement. Flow and organic movement. Study and use of weight, momentum, impulse, swing and flow of movement, developing the body's kinetic intelligence. How grounding works, how to stay connected to the floor through the study of body structure (bones and joints), of weight and use of breath. Organic movement and its impact to the body, use of own body structure in the most efficient way. -Connectivity practice. Spacial and body awareness. Connectivity is studied both in terms of a fully connected moving body and of a mover in a state of full connection with his/her environment. How the body moves in its full awareness, connecting and interacting with its environment - the other people, the space, the floor- and its own inner state at the same time. Spatial and body awareness, together with connectivity practice, helps to develop a unified physical and mental consciousness, thus a moving body in its full consciousness expressing itself in space and time. Throughout the class fixed phrases and exercises are given, practicing the aforementioned elements. The material is highly physical and classes often end up on a longer phrase practice, built from the accumulation of smaller exercises, working also on physical strength, stamina and memory.

name: The Way Back Home - JOY Space
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'The Way Back Home - JOY Space', 'description': 'Yoga for The Way Back Home to ourSelves: A yoga and meditation practice rooted in nondual tantra philosophy, for revealing and (re)connecting to your true, essential nature, and for exploring ways of honouring your essence and its authentic expression. In nonduality, there is a recognition that everything in the universe, including ourselves, is Divine. And in tantra, this world we live in and perceive is not written off as an illusion, but rather embraced and worked with, also holding the potential to lead us back to the Divine. We will explore these philosophies more deeply through practice and our own direct experiences. Styles of practice include self-enquiry meditation, a meditative hatha, and a more somatic flow highlighting intuitive movement. If you‚Äôve felt a longing to connect more intimately to the expansive depth of your being through yoga, come practice with me :) Open to all levels.', 'address': {'@type': 'PostalAddress', 'addressLocality': 'Berlin, Germany', 'addressCountry': 'Germany', 'postalCode': '10117', 'streetAddress': 'Albrechtstra√üe 19'}, 'telephone': '+44 13109383645', 'geo': {'@type': 'GeoCoordinates', 'latitude': '52.5224586', 'longitude': '13.3844949'}, 'priceRange': '-', 'image': 'https://storage.googleapis.com/download/storage/v1/b/usc-pro-uscweb-live-media/o/de-live%2Foriginal_3629x2041_3c7e38b8d51d-R1_05237_0006_1692002929871046_admin.jpg?generation=1692002930067239&alt=media'}

metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Triathlon Crew Berlin', 'description': 'Willkommen bei der Triathloncrew Berlin. Entsprechend gibt es unter den Sportlern kaum jemanden der Experte in allen drei Disziplinen ist. Dieses Problem wollen wir von der Triathloncrew Berlin l√∂sen. name: VINYASA FLOW YOGA (mit Naudia)
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'VINYASA FLOW YOGA (mit Naudia)', 'description': 'VINYASA YOGA 1-ON-1 & CHINESE MASSAGE (MIT NAUDIA) VINYASA FLOW 1-ON-1 In this 40-60 minute class, I will personally work with you to identify areas for improvement as well as clarify your individual goals. Vinyasa yoga is a style of yoga that focuses on conscious breathing while moving through postures, which help improve strength and increase flexibility. Together we will identify your areas for improvement in your existing practice - to enhance your yoga in the studio and at home. Location will depend on time of day and weather conditions. After you have made an appointment with me, please meet me first at Ebersstr. 7 10827 and, if the weather permits, the class will take place in a lovely little park outside. *Please bring a yoga mat, towel and water ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ CHINESE DEEP TISSUE MASSAGE Chinese deep tissue massage is known for releasing areas of tension by going deep into the musculature. This type of massage focuses on relaxation of the muscle tissue, which can reduce pain and stiffness, as well as improve range of motion and general mobility. Also, massaging acupressure points releases blocked energy in the body, mobilizing chi for health and well-being. name: Alkimia Yoga - Yoga & Meditation with Zarahlena
metadata: {'@context': 'http://schema.org', '@type': 'LocalBusiness', 'name': 'Alkimia Yoga - Yoga & Meditation with Zarahlena ', 'description': 'ENG: Alkimia Yoga finds its home on board the beautiful boat "Kulturschiff Paula" against the backdrop of Lake Rummelsburg at the half-island Stralau in Berlin-Friedrichshain. Classes on the boat are held indoors in cold weather and on deck when the sun is shining. Discover more about upcoming workshops and retreats in various locations this year at www.alkimia.yoga.
